    ```java
public int pivotIndex(int[] nums) {
    int total_sum = 0, left_sum = 0;
    for (int num : nums)
        total_sum += num;
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; ++i) {
        if (left_sum == total_sum - left_sum - nums[i])
            return i;
        left_sum += nums[i];
    }
    return -1;
}
```


    1. First, find the total sum of the array.
2. Iterate through the array, maintaining a running sum of the elements to the left of the current index.
3. For each index, check if the left sum is equal to the total sum minus the left sum and the value at the current index.
4. If such equality is found, return the index as the pivot index. If not found, return -1.
